OL,3,CWarm weather and Mother's Day spending
OL,4,Cgives retailers March boost
OL,6,FRetailers enjoyed some "green shoots"
OL,7,Fof consumer confidence in March as
OL,8,Fgardening products and Mother's Day
OL,9,Fgifts flew off the shelves, new
OL,10,Ffigures show.
OL,12,FTotal UK retail sales were up 1.1%
OL,13,Fyear on year, despite Easter's later
OL,14,Farrival this year distorting the
OL,15,Ffigures, according to the British
OL,16,FRetail Consortium (BRC)-KPMG Retail
OL,17,FSales Monitor.
OL,19,FNevertheless, food sales were still up
OL,20,Fby 1.6% on last March, while non-food
OL,21,Fsales increased by 0.6%.
