OL,3,CWarm weather and Mother's Day spending
OL,4,Cgives retailers March boost
OL,6,FBRC chief executive Helen Dickinson
OL,7,Fsaid: "Despite a challenging global
OL,8,Fgeopolitical landscape, the small
OL,9,Fincrease in both food and non-food
OL,10,Fsales masked signs of underlying
OL,11,Fstrengthening of demand given March
OL,12,F2025's comparison with last year's
OL,13,Fearly Easter."
OL,15,FLinda Ellett, UK head of consumer,
OL,16,Fretail and leisure at KPMG, said: "As
OL,17,Fspring weather arrived, house- and
OL,18,Fgarden-related purchases and gifts for
OL,19,FMother's Day drove retail sales growth
OL,20,Fin March.
