OL,3,CWarm weather and Mother's Day spending
OL,4,Cgives retailers March boost
OL,6,F"Amidst downbeat consumer confidence
OL,7,Fin the UK's economic outlook, and many
OL,8,Fhouseholds facing rising costs, retail
OL,9,Fsales growth feels an achievement.
OL,11,F"But with non-food sales only climbing
OL,12,Faround 1% on average, competition
OL,13,Fmeans there are some retailers really
OL,14,Fstruggling whilst others win,
OL,15,Fespecially online."
OL,17,FSeparate figures from Barclays show
OL,18,Fconsumer card spending grew 0.5% year
OL,19,Fon year in March, down from February's
OL,20,F1%.
