OL,3,CWarm weather and Mother's Day spending
OL,4,Cgives retailers March boost
OL,6,FThe sunny weather boosted non-
OL,7,Fessential categories such as garden
OL,8,Fcentres and food and drink specialist
OL,9,Fstores, although consumers cut back on
OL,10,Fessential spending by 2.9% as they
OL,11,Fanticipated rising household bills.
OL,13,FA survey for the bank's Consumer Spend
OL,14,Freport found two in three UK adults
OL,15,F(67%) are concerned about the impact
OL,16,Fon their household finances of recent
OL,17,Fstock market volatility due to trade
OL,18,Ftariffs, while 71% plan to buy more
OL,19,F"Made in Britain" products.
